Israeli Stocks: Teva Pharmaceutical Industries and Perrigo

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-04-26T14:10:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/israeli-stocks-teva-pharmaceutical-industries-and-perrigo.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index declined 0.7
percent, the most since April 7, to 1,333.14 at the 4:30 p.m.
close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 1.65 billion shekels
($483 million) in shares and convertible securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Perrigo Co. (PRGO)   rose the most in more than a week,
gaining 0.7 percent to 303.20 shekels. The maker of over-the-
counter drugs said a U.S. appeals court affirmed an earlier
decision that Mead Johnson had engaged in false advertising
resulting in an injunction prohibiting it from making similar
claims and awarding damages in favor of Perrigo’s infant formula
unit.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)   slid to the
lowest since November 2008, falling 4.7 percent to 157.80
shekels. The shares retreated 7 percent in the U.S., while
Israeli markets were closed for a holiday.  Biogen Idec Inc. (BIIB) 
reported results from a study of its multiple sclerosis pill BG-
12 that exceeded analysts’ expectations. The world’s largest
maker of generic drugs said results of clinical trials on
multiple sclerosis treatments can’t be compared unless agents
are tested in a head-to-head manner in the same trial.  To contact the reporter on this story:
{Ronit Goodman} in Tel Aviv at 
